To 16 mL of boiled distilled water, add 3 mL of solution B and mix gently with hand. Add 2 mL of solution A and mix gently with hand. A milky precipitate will form. Add, dropwise, 4 mL of solution C while mixing gently with hand. The precipitate must disappear completely. If not, discard and start over. Dispatch in 2- or 5-mL syringes with a 0.22-μm filter at the tip of the syringe. Stable for several months at 4°C. Discard if nonspecific fine precipitates are observed on the thin sections under the EM.

