with early endosomes or with lysosomes (see Fig. 3D,E,G), and the second is used to classify phagosomes as resembling either early endosomes or lysosomes (see, e.g., refs. 7 and 11 for illustration of method; see also Note 7 for other possible markers).
1. Prepare a concentrated solution of HRP in culture medium (RPMI or DMEM). 2. Dilute HRP in complete medium. Prepare the solution fresh, warm up to 37°C, and use immediately (see Note 8 for appropriate concentration).

